Sankalpa Specification — Licensing
==================================

This repository contains two kinds of material under two licenses. The split
is intentional and is recorded in ADR-0003.

1. SPECIFICATION TEXT (prose in spec/, rfcs/, adrs/, aeps/, process/, research/,
   and all Markdown documentation) is licensed under:

       Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
       https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

   You may share and adapt the text for any purpose, provided you give
   appropriate credit to the Sankalpa project.

2. CODE SAMPLES, SCHEMAS, TEMPLATES, and DIAGRAM SOURCES (fenced code blocks,
   files under templates/ and diagrams/src/, and any example configuration) are
   licensed under:

       Apache License, Version 2.0
       https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

   A NOTICE file will accompany released implementation artifacts.

Rationale: prose deserves a documentation license optimized for attribution and
reuse; executable/machine-consumable material deserves a permissive software
license with an explicit patent grant. Keeping them separate avoids the common
trap of licensing a specification under terms designed for software.

SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0 AND Apache-2.0
